<heading id="D0F181E71979FFBE6A8BA1C07162FE55" bold="true" box="[189,334,423,449]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B972EA991979FFBE6A8BA1C07162FE55" bold="true" box="[189,334,423,449]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1979FFBE6ADCA1BE7106FE67" blockId="89.[189,732,473,538]" box="[234,298,473,499]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis id="B972EA991979FFBE6ADCA1BE7106FE67" bold="true" box="[234,298,473,499]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1979FFBE6A8BA26772F0FD8E" blockId="89.[189,732,473,538]" box="[189,732,512,538]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
LENGTH. Body 6.6–7.0 mm, wing 
<quantity id="4CFE9B6E1979FFBE687EA26772F4FD8E" box="[584,728,512,538]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="5.8" valueMin="5.2">5.2–5.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1979FFBE6A8BA22E7505FC55" blockId="89.[189,1399,585,961]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
HEAD. Face in lateral view concave, strongly projected antero-ventrally; frontal prominence strongly developed. Ratio width of vertex at anterior ocellus: width of head 1: 5.3; ratio width of ocellar triangle: width of vertex 1: 1.6; ratio length of ocellar triangle: length of frons 1: 2.0. Face black, ventral half yellow; light grey pollinose, long pilose along eye-margin. Hypostomal bridge dark yellow, long pale pilose. Gena and mouth edge yellow with large subtriangular non-pollinose shiny area. Frons and vertex black, slightly pollinose, a narrow subtriangular area posterior of lunula non-pollinose and shiny (
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1979FFBE6AF0A3557114FCD8" box="[198,312,818,844]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="86.[189,232,1787,1813]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,412,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@86.[189,1399,412,1739]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="Fig. 38. Head, lateral view (C, K), dorsal view (A–B, D, F–J, L) and frontal view (E). A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) farinosa sp. nov.,holotype, Ƌ, Sabah, Malaysia. B. S. (A.) fimbriata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Thailand. C–D. S. (A.) forceps Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, Ƌ, Myanmar. E. S. (A.) furva Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, Ƌ, Myanmar. F. S. (A.) ghatsi, sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, India. G. S. (A.) gigantea sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. H. S. (A.) granditarsis sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Thailand. I. S. (A.) hamulata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, India. J. S. (A.) hansoni Thompson, 1966, holotype, Ƌ, Nepal. K–L. S. (A.) hauseri sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Nepal. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830632/files/figure.png" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Fig. 38H</figureCitation>
); pile short, light yellow. Frons with deep pit anteromedially and wide but weak medial furrow. Occiput black, light grey pollinose, light yellow pilose. Eye without enlarged facets at anterior margin. Antenna dark yellow to brown with black setae dorsally on scape and pedicel; basoflagellomere elongate, ratio width: length 1: 1.7; arista long pilose, about 2 times as long as basoflagellomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1979FFBE6A8BA3977181FB31" blockId="89.[189,1399,1008,1189]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">THORAX. Colour black, postpronotum and dorso-medial part of anepisternum and anepimeron yellow; weakly greyish pollinose, pleuron entirely more heavily grey pollinose; scutum and pleuron with very short adpressed light yellow pile. Scutellum semicircular, black, shiny, with pile slightly longer than on scutum, with two widely set, very short setae medially at posterior margin, ratio length of scutellum: length of seta 1: 0.7.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1979FFBE6A8BA4B3722EFAA8" blockId="89.[189,1398,1236,1340]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">WING. Entirely microtrichose; hyaline, stigma yellowish, membrane brown infuscated at junction of veins R2+3 and R4+5, along veins bm-cu, r-m, M1 and on the wing apex. Crossvein dm-cu meeting vein M perpendicularly and vein M</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1979FFBE6834A5527227FAD7" box="[514,523,1333,1347]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">1</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1979FFBE6824A54572EAFAA8" blockId="89.[189,1398,1236,1340]" box="[530,710,1314,1340]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">meeting vein R</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1979FFBE68F3A55272CCFAD7" box="[709,736,1333,1347]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">4+5</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1979FFBE68D1A5457389FAA8" blockId="89.[189,1398,1236,1340]" box="[743,933,1314,1340]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">perpendicularly.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1979FFBE6A8BA50C748AF9D3" blockId="89.[189,1399,1387,1607]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
LEGS. Proleg yellow, tarsomere 1 black on apical half and tarsomeres 2–5 entirely black; protarsus, 
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1979FFBE6A8BA5F5710AFA38" box="[189,294,1426,1452]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="128.[189,232,1893,1919]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1009,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@128.[189,1399,1009,1848]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="Fig. 61. Protarsus, dorsal view. A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) atrimanus sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Vietnam. B. S. (A.) granditarsis sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. C. S. (A.) incretonigra sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Vietnam. D. S. (A.) nigrotarsata sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. E. S. (A.) orientalis Kertész, 1914, Ƌ, Taiwan. F. S. (A.) plautus sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. Scale bars 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5678327" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5678327/files/figure.png" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Fig. 61B</figureCitation>
, enlarged and flattened, ratio apical width of tibia: width of tarsomere 2 1: 1.8; basitarsomere about as long as combined length of tarsomeres 2 and 3. Metaleg with coxa black, trochanter yellow; femur black with basal 1/5 yellow, slightly incrassate and club shaped, ratio width: length 1: 5.3, anteroventrally with long white pile, pile almost twice as long as black setae; tibia black and yellow biannulate, without apicoventral dens; tarsus entirely black, basitarsomere thick, ratio width: length 1: 3.1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1979FFBE6A8BA611726CF8ED" blockId="89.[189,1399,1654,1913]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
ABDOMEN. Length ratio of terga I: II: III: IV 1: 2.9: 2.0: 1.5; ratio width at posterior margin: medial length of tergum II and III 1: 3.0 and 1: 1.4. Terga black, anterior 1/5 of tergum III with yellow fascia; pile pale, on terga short, laterally on terga I and II long; tergum I with 2 widely separated, strong, light yellow setae at lateral margin; sternum III not sclerotized; sternum IV, 
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1979FFBE69ADA68C7429F891" box="[923,1029,1771,1797]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="88.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,554,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@88.[189,1399,548,1903]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="Fig. 39. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) granditarsis sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Posterior part of sternum IV, ventral view. B. Aedeagus, right side lateral view. C. Left surstylus, lateral view. D. Sternum IX and superior lobe, left side lateral view. E. Genitalia right side lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830634/files/figure.png" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Fig. 39A</figureCitation>
; sterna VI, VII and VIII simple, with long yellow pile. Genitalia, 
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1979FFBE6867A7767284F8BF" box="[593,680,1809,1835]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="88.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,554,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@88.[189,1399,548,1903]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="Fig. 39. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) granditarsis sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Posterior part of sternum IV, ventral view. B. Aedeagus, right side lateral view. C. Left surstylus, lateral view. D. Sternum IX and superior lobe, left side lateral view. E. Genitalia right side lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830634/files/figure.png" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
B–E: note the very long setose pile on cercus, symmetrical surstyli and superior lobes and the small setae on the membrane between the ventral margin of tergum IX and the gonostylar apodemes.
</paragraph>
